<title>CHINA: Everbright Bank of China to launch US$64 mln loan.</title>
<headline>Everbright Bank of China to launch US$64 mln loan.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-07-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Everbright Bank of China has mandated four banks to arrange a US$64 million five-year loan, bankers said.</p>
<p>The loan has been fully underwritten by the arrangers - Chase Manhattan Asia, Deutsche Bank, Bayerische Landesbank and ING Barings. A roadshow is scheduled next week.</p>
<p>Major shareholders of the bank are China Everbright-IHD Pacific Ltd and China Everbright Group, which is controlled by China's State Council.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
